name: Caramel Chunk Brownies
author: Reynolds Kitchens(R)
summary: Caramel and chocolate come together for this super simple and succulent dessert!
ingredients: 1 cup hot caramel dessert topping, divided
1 (11.5 ounce) package semi-sweet chocolate chunks, divided
directions: Line a 13x9x2-inch baking pan with Reynolds® Parchment Paper, extending paper up sides of pan; set aside
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions
Pour half of batter into pan
Cover with half of caramel topping, chocolate chunks and almonds
Pour in the remaining brownie batter
Drop remaining caramel by rounded teaspoons onto brownie batter
Top with remaining chocolate chunks and almonds
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until edges are set
Remove and let tray cool completely in pan
Use edges of parchment to lift brownies from pan onto a cutting board
Pull back edges of parchment for easy cutting
